1
00:00:01.501 --> 00:00:03.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When are they expecting you in Brazil?

2
00:00:03.586 --> 00:00:05.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told them a couple weeks
after the ceremony.

3
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:08.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With all the receptions,
and then I'll need at least a week

4
00:00:08.925 --> 00:00:10.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to clear up the linguistic database.

5
00:00:10.844 --> 00:00:12.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
After 10 years on this ship,

6
00:00:12.470 --> 00:00:15.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I bet it'll take a while getting
used to the humidity again.

7
00:00:15.557 --> 00:00:16.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And the bugs.

8
00:00:17.434 --> 00:00:19.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Does the captain have to give a speech?

9
00:00:19.477 --> 00:00:20.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's working on it now.

10
00:00:21.312 --> 00:00:23.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He hates giving speeches.

11
00:00:23.148 --> 00:00:26.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He'll undoubtedly make every
effort to take no credit.

12
00:00:26.359 --> 00:00:27.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Undoubtedly.

13
00:00:27.610 --> 00:00:30.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That'd be like zefram cochrane
not taking credit for warp drive.

14
00:00:31.239 --> 00:00:34.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How do you pronounce the name
of the second tellarite liberator?

15
00:00:34.617 --> 00:00:36.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Challash?
-Shallash.

16
00:00:37.328 --> 00:00:38.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shallash. Thanks.

17
00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:40.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How's it going, sir?

18
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:40.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whatever I write,

19
00:00:41.082 --> 00:00:42.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it sounds like I'm trying
to take credit for this.

20
00:00:43.084 --> 00:00:47.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, Admiral Douglas is asking you
to approve the decommission protocols.

21
00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:49.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One thing at a time.
After the charter's signed,

22
00:00:49.883 --> 00:00:52.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll give him whatever he needs
to put <i>Enterprise </i>in mothballs.

23
00:00:52.719 --> 00:00:55.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[crewman]<i> All senior staff,</i>
<i>report to the Bridge.</i>

24
00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:57.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Riker] Computer, freeze program.

25
00:00:58.850 --> 00:01:00.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Save from this time index.

26
00:01:01.102 --> 00:01:02.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[computer] <i>Program saved.</i>

27
00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:04.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
End program.

28
00:01:16.743 --> 00:01:19.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ It's been a long road ♪</i>

29
00:01:21.414 --> 00:01:24.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Getting from there to here ♪</i>

30
00:01:24.375 --> 00:01:26.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ It's been a long time ♪</i>

31
00:01:28.171 --> 00:01:31.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ But my time is finally near ♪</i>

32
00:01:32.383 --> 00:01:36.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ And I will see my dream</i>
<i>Come alive at last ♪</i>

33
00:01:36.679 --> 00:01:40.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I will touch the sky ♪</i>

34
00:01:40.099 --> 00:01:43.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>♪ And they're not gonna</i>
<i>Hold me down no more ♪</i>

35
00:01:43.978 --> 00:01:46.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ No, they're not gonna change my mind ♪</i>

36
00:01:47.106 --> 00:01:49.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ 'Cause I've got faith ♪</i>

37
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:51.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ Of the heart ♪</i>

38
00:01:52.112 --> 00:01:54.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ I'm going where my heart will take me ♪</i>

39
00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:58.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I've got faith to believe ♪</i>

40
00:01:59.786 --> 00:02:02.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ I can do anything ♪</i>

41
00:02:02.789 --> 00:02:06.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>♪ I've got strength of the soul ♪</i>

42
00:02:06.668 --> 00:02:10.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ And no one's gonna bend or break me ♪</i>

43
00:02:10.421 --> 00:02:14.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I can reach any star ♪</i>

44
00:02:15.885 --> 00:02:17.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I've got faith ♪</i>

45
00:02:17.387 --> 00:02:18.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I've got, I've got ♪</i>

46
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:22.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>-♪ I've got ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I've got faith ♪</i>

47
00:02:23.726 --> 00:02:27.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Faith of the heart ♪</i>

48
00:02:36.614 --> 00:02:41.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Riker] <i>First officer's personal log,</i>
<i>Stardate 47457.1.</i>

49
00:02:41.494 --> 00:02:44.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>With the unexpected arrival of</i>
<i>Admiral Pressman, my old C.O.,</i>

50
00:02:45.081 --> 00:02:47.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I find myself in an awkward position.</i>

51
00:02:48.042 --> 00:02:50.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Counselor Troi has suggested</i>
<i>I might get a few insights</i>

52
00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:53.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>by calling up an historic holoprogram.</i>

53
00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:03.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Troi] Are you sure you don't want to
talk about what happened?

54
00:03:03.558 --> 00:03:05.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've told you everything I can.

55
00:03:05.685 --> 00:03:07.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If it's a question
of breaking a promise...

56
00:03:07.854 --> 00:03:09.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Not a promise. An order.

57
00:03:10.148 --> 00:03:12.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Have you learned anything
on the holodeck about breaking orders?

58
00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:14.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Not yet.

59
00:03:14.110 --> 00:03:16.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've gone back a couple of days
earlier to get a perspective.

60
00:03:16.571 --> 00:03:18.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
But I really don't see
how this is gonna help.

61
00:03:19.741 --> 00:03:22.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
That's why you run a starship,
and I'm a counselor.

62
00:03:24.954 --> 00:03:26.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Reed's shorter than I thought he'd be.

63
00:03:26.748 --> 00:03:27.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Maybe the program's off.

64
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:29.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
No, I'm sure it's fine.

65
00:03:29.208 --> 00:03:30.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It's just, you expect
larger-than-life people

66
00:03:31.085 --> 00:03:32.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
to be larger-than-life.

67
00:03:32.837 --> 00:03:34.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-Has the Andorian hailed them?
-Not yet.

68
00:03:34.923 --> 00:03:36.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You might want to leap ahead
to that point.

69
00:03:36.925 --> 00:03:38.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It's where things start really happening.

70
00:03:38.509 --> 00:03:40.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
And you should consider
taking over the galley.

71
00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:41.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Why?

72
00:03:42.013 --> 00:03:44.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, Starfleet ships didn't
have counselors in those days,

73
00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:47.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
But the chef on the first
<i>Enterprise </i>came pretty close.

74
00:03:48.061 --> 00:03:50.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I read almost everybody confided in him.

75
00:03:50.772 --> 00:03:52.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'll keep that in mind.

76
00:03:52.232 --> 00:03:53.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-Supper?
-You bet.

77
00:03:53.691 --> 00:03:55.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-I'll give you an update.
-OK.

78
00:03:59.906 --> 00:04:01.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
That's impossible.

79
00:04:02.367 --> 00:04:04.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Shran's been dead for what, three years?

80
00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:05.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[beeping]

81
00:04:09.874 --> 00:04:11.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
This is quite a surprise.

82
00:04:11.834 --> 00:04:14.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I'm sorry, pink-skin,</i> <i>but it was essential</i>

83
00:04:14.587 --> 00:04:16.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>certain people believed</i>
<i>I had met my demise.</i>

84
00:04:17.131 --> 00:04:18.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Including me.

85
00:04:18.466 --> 00:04:21.886 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I know it's been a while,</i> <i>but as I recall,</i>
<i>you still owe me a favor.</i>

86
00:04:23.179 --> 00:04:24.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I remember.

87
00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:27.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But this isn't a good time, Shran.

88
00:04:27.767 --> 00:04:29.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I assume you know where we're heading.

89
00:04:29.352 --> 00:04:31.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I may no longer be a member</i>
<i>of the imperial guard,</i>

90
00:04:31.562 --> 00:04:33.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but I'm aware of</i> <i>the proposed coalition.</i>

91
00:04:33.815 --> 00:04:35.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's more than a proposal.

92
00:04:35.525 --> 00:04:37.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're on our way to earth
to sign the charter.

93
00:04:37.735 --> 00:04:39.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The ceremony</i> <i>isn't for three days.</i>

94
00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:41.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If my plan works,</i>
<i>you'll be home in plenty of time.</i>

95
00:04:42.156 --> 00:04:43.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[scoffs]

96
00:04:44.242 --> 00:04:47.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid a detour is out
of the question right now.

97
00:04:47.537 --> 00:04:49.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>My child's been abducted!</i>

98
00:04:50.248 --> 00:04:54.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Kidnapped. You owe me.</i>

99
00:04:54.794 --> 00:04:56.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You never told me you had a child.

100
00:04:56.963 --> 00:05:01.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Jhamel gave birth</i> <i>five years ago.</i>
<i>A daughter.</i> <i>They've taken her.</i>

101
00:05:01.843 --> 00:05:02.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who?

102
00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:07.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former associates.</i> <i>It's a long story.</i>
<i>You need to let me</i> <i>come aboard.</i>

103
00:05:13.396 --> 00:05:14.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Set a rendezvous course.

104
00:05:14.772 --> 00:05:16.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, freeze program.

105
00:05:16.149 --> 00:05:17.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeps]

106
00:05:17.942 --> 00:05:19.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Advance ahead one hour.

107
00:05:20.403 --> 00:05:21.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Switch to objective mode.

108
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:33.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Shran] Who would have thought
civilian life would be more dangerous

109
00:05:33.416 --> 00:05:35.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than commanding a ship
for the imperial guard.

110
00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:38.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I still don't understand why you left.
You were a hero.

111
00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:40.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A hero with a family.

112
00:05:42.258 --> 00:05:46.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I always believed
that change was a good thing.

113
00:05:46.095 --> 00:05:47.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was a fool.

114
00:05:47.513 --> 00:05:51.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why would you fake your own death?
-I made some poor choices.

115
00:05:51.851 --> 00:05:53.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Picked the wrong friends,

116
00:05:54.395 --> 00:05:57.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
people involved in questionable
business ventures.

117
00:05:57.690 --> 00:06:00.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They think I took something
that belonged to them.

118
00:06:01.444 --> 00:06:04.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With the help of some old
colleagues from the guard,

119
00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:06.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I managed to make myself disappear.

120
00:06:07.116 --> 00:06:10.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It worked... for nearly three years.

121
00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:14.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Your friends found you?
-Six months ago.

122
00:06:14.582 --> 00:06:16.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've been on the move ever since.

123
00:06:17.335 --> 00:06:19.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They took her in the middle of the night.

124
00:06:20.296 --> 00:06:23.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was in the next room, asleep!

125
00:06:24.383 --> 00:06:25.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Useless!

126
00:06:27.428 --> 00:06:28.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's been a week.

127
00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:33.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They say if I don't return
what's theirs, they'll kill her.

128
00:06:34.268 --> 00:06:35.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then give them what they want.

129
00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:38.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't have it! I never did.

130
00:06:39.357 --> 00:06:40.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you have a plan.

131
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:44.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shran] It cost me everything I had,

132
00:06:44.195 --> 00:06:47.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I managed to find out
where they've taken her.

133
00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:50.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're on a trading outpost, Rigel X.

134
00:06:50.535 --> 00:06:53.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I'm familiar with it.
-I know these men quite well, Captain.

135
00:06:53.913 --> 00:06:57.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can outwit them. I've done it before.
But I'll need at least seven men.

136
00:06:58.543 --> 00:07:03.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to help me. It's my little girl.

137
00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:06.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's an admitted criminal.
You said so yourself.

138
00:07:06.634 --> 00:07:08.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He said he fell in
with some disreputable people.

139
00:07:08.928 --> 00:07:10.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That doesn't make him a criminal.

140
00:07:10.471 --> 00:07:13.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we're late for the ceremony,
it'll have far-reaching consequences.

141
00:07:13.307 --> 00:07:14.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If Shran hadn't helped us,

142
00:07:14.851 --> 00:07:16.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never would have gotten aboard
the Xindi weapon.

143
00:07:16.686 --> 00:07:17.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you forgotten that?

144
00:07:18.062 --> 00:07:20.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This alliance is based
on friendship and loyalty,

145
00:07:20.898 --> 00:07:22.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
exactly what Shran is
looking for right now.

146
00:07:22.900 --> 00:07:23.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't trust him.

147
00:07:23.901 --> 00:07:25.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You don't trust Andorians. You never have.

148
00:07:25.987 --> 00:07:29.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank god the Vulcan council
is a little more enlightened than you are.

149
00:07:29.282 --> 00:07:31.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If they're willing to forge
an alliance with Andoria,

150
00:07:31.117 --> 00:07:33.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the least you can do is give
Shran the benefit of the doubt.

151
00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:38.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When we met 10 years ago,
I didn't trust you.

152
00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:41.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For that matter,
I didn't trust any Vulcans.

153
00:07:41.544 --> 00:07:44.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You helped me get past that, remember?

154
00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:47.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I listened to you.
Now it's your turn to listen to me.

155
00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:50.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can't turn my back on him, T'pol.

156
00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:54.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Try to understand.
-I'll try.

157
00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:56.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] By the way...

158
00:07:58.853 --> 00:08:00.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Drop by the galley when you get a moment.

159
00:08:01.397 --> 00:08:04.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chef's trying to come up with a menu
for our last dinner together.

160
00:08:04.984 --> 00:08:06.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He wants to know
everybody's favorite dish.

161
00:08:07.361 --> 00:08:09.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[T'pol] There are 83 crew members aboard.

162
00:08:09.864 --> 00:08:11.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just go see him, all right?

163
00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:15.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whining]

164
00:08:16.329 --> 00:08:17.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] Don't worry.

165
00:08:18.206 --> 00:08:20.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chef's promised
at least six kinds of cheese.

166
00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:24.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[T'pol] I appreciate the gesture,

167
00:08:24.253 --> 00:08:27.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it's not necessary to
prepare a special dish for me.

168
00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:28.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on.

169
00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:31.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've already started to reduce
the plomeek broth.

170
00:08:31.928 --> 00:08:34.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All I need to know is
which roots you prefer.

171
00:08:34.722 --> 00:08:37.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In that case, I prefer to be surprised.

172
00:08:37.391 --> 00:08:39.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pull up a chair. I could use the company.

173
00:08:41.729 --> 00:08:45.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I heard a rumor I may be whipping up
some Andorian cabbage soup tonight.

174
00:08:45.858 --> 00:08:49.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have already lost five hours
picking up Shran's shuttle.

175
00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:51.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now we're going to lose
at least another day

176
00:08:51.155 --> 00:08:53.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
diverting our course to Rigel.

177
00:08:53.282 --> 00:08:54.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His child's in danger.

178
00:08:55.785 --> 00:08:58.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is there anything aboard
this ship you don't know?

179
00:08:58.663 --> 00:09:01.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jonathan is a compassionate man.
You should know that by now.

180
00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:05.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His compassion has gotten us
into trouble on many occasions.

181
00:09:06.170 --> 00:09:08.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We could miss this ceremony.

182
00:09:08.297 --> 00:09:10.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't worry. I've got a hunch
you're gonna make it.

183
00:09:11.008 --> 00:09:12.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Tea?
-Thank you.

184
00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:17.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Phlox has given me his largest
Edosian suckerfish.

185
00:09:17.974 --> 00:09:18.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

186
00:09:20.059 --> 00:09:22.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like a catfish.
I'm hoping it tastes like one.

187
00:09:23.396 --> 00:09:25.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander Tucker's crazy for catfish.

188
00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:27.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you ever miss him?

189
00:09:28.150 --> 00:09:31.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I spent the morning with him,
recalibrating the plasma array.

190
00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:32.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what I mean.

191
00:09:32.947 --> 00:09:36.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you're referring
to our intimate relationship,

192
00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:37.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that's been over for six years.

193
00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:40.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But the question remains, do you miss him?

194
00:09:40.538 --> 00:09:43.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm Vulcan. I don't miss people.

195
00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:45.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry. I forgot.

196
00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:48.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is he as concerned as you
about making this ceremony?

197
00:09:48.296 --> 00:09:50.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Trip rarely questions
the Captain's decisions.

198
00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:53.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He doesn't strike me as someone
who follows orders blindly.

199
00:09:54.343 --> 00:09:55.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's not.

200
00:09:55.261 --> 00:09:58.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He simply tends to agree with
the Captain most of the time.

201
00:09:58.180 --> 00:09:59.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He trusts him.

202
00:10:01.517 --> 00:10:02.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Would you peel these for me?

203
00:10:07.773 --> 00:10:09.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Before I joined this crew,

204
00:10:09.150 --> 00:10:12.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I never could have imagined anything
more important than following orders.

205
00:10:12.361 --> 00:10:13.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And now?

206
00:10:14.989 --> 00:10:18.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Humans believe that sometimes
you have to follow your instincts.

207
00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:23.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Very illogical approach,
but one I've come to embrace.

208
00:10:26.208 --> 00:10:28.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Computer, freeze program.
-[computer beeps]

209
00:10:29.587 --> 00:10:30.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks.

210
00:10:42.016 --> 00:10:43.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

211
00:10:52.777 --> 00:10:53.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

212
00:10:54.278 --> 00:10:55.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There you are.

213
00:10:57.073 --> 00:10:58.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Someone you know?

214
00:10:58.491 --> 00:10:59.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Someone I knew.

215
00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:01.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Pegasus?</i>

216
00:11:01.827 --> 00:11:05.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Phil Wallace. Hell of a handball player.

217
00:11:05.247 --> 00:11:07.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pressman was getting ready to promote him.

218
00:11:07.541 --> 00:11:09.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many died?

219
00:11:09.877 --> 00:11:12.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Seventy one. All but nine of us.

220
00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:15.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How do you feel about learning
the ship wasn't destroyed?

221
00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:18.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What difference does it make?
71 people died.

222
00:11:20.471 --> 00:11:22.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're feeling guilty.

223
00:11:23.224 --> 00:11:25.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think, in some way,
you were responsible?

224
00:11:25.893 --> 00:11:28.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're the empath. Why don't you tell me?

225
00:11:30.064 --> 00:11:33.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think it's something else,
something about seeing that ship again.

226
00:11:34.402 --> 00:11:37.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why don't we change the subject? OK?
-OK.

227
00:11:38.948 --> 00:11:40.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did things go on the holodeck?

228
00:11:41.409 --> 00:11:43.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They picked up the Andorian.
They're on their way to Rigel X.

229
00:11:43.953 --> 00:11:46.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was referring to any insight
you may have gained.

230
00:11:46.914 --> 00:11:50.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I took your advice about the chef.
You were right. T'pol opened up to me.

231
00:11:50.626 --> 00:11:54.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Have you met with Commander Tucker?
-No, I haven't made it to Engineering yet.

232
00:11:54.505 --> 00:11:57.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Have you spent any time on the NX-01?
-I've never run the program.

233
00:11:57.883 --> 00:11:59.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about the ship itself?

234
00:11:59.218 --> 00:12:03.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I went when I was a little girl,
but I get all those museum ships mixed up.

235
00:12:03.889 --> 00:12:06.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now's your chance. Come on down with me.

236
00:12:06.475 --> 00:12:08.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have an appointment in an hour.

237
00:12:08.102 --> 00:12:10.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll get you back in plenty of time.
Come on.

238
00:12:12.022 --> 00:12:13.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Our Brig is bigger than this.

239
00:12:13.566 --> 00:12:16.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A lot of things change in 200 years.
Watch yourself!

240
00:12:16.986 --> 00:12:17.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No fish tank.

241
00:12:17.945 --> 00:12:20.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How could archer survive
without a fish tank?

242
00:12:23.117 --> 00:12:24.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Allow me.

243
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:30.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He does have a dog, though.

244
00:12:30.875 --> 00:12:33.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right, I remember. One of the musketeers.

245
00:12:33.586 --> 00:12:34.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Porthos.

246
00:12:35.463 --> 00:12:36.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, comfy.

247
00:12:36.922 --> 00:12:38.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No seat for the first officer?

248
00:12:39.049 --> 00:12:42.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps, Archer wasn't as fussy
as Captain Picard,

249
00:12:42.303 --> 00:12:44.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when it came to people
sitting in his chair.

250
00:12:46.182 --> 00:12:48.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

251
00:12:48.434 --> 00:12:50.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I remember seeing one of these
in a photograph.

252
00:12:50.603 --> 00:12:54.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kirk's ship had them, I think.
Engineering's down this way.

253
00:12:54.565 --> 00:12:57.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's something lonely about
a ship without its crew.

254
00:12:57.610 --> 00:13:00.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, add an appropriate
crew complement, objective mode.

255
00:13:00.696 --> 00:13:02.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

256
00:13:02.406 --> 00:13:03.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's better.

257
00:13:04.825 --> 00:13:09.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you recall, Rigel X is filled
with a very unsavory element.

258
00:13:09.246 --> 00:13:12.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I rather doubt Shran's scheme
will be quite as simple as he claims.

259
00:13:12.750 --> 00:13:14.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can't imagine the Captain would put us

260
00:13:14.585 --> 00:13:16.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in jeopardy this close
to signing the charter.

261
00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:18.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I don't like it.
-[electronic humming]

262
00:13:19.215 --> 00:13:20.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What exactly are you doing?

263
00:13:21.258 --> 00:13:24.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These injectors need to be
purged every six months.

264
00:13:25.137 --> 00:13:27.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are the deuterium filters clear?

265
00:13:27.556 --> 00:13:29.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-We've done all but three.
-All right.

266
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Make it quick.
-Aye, sir.

267
00:13:32.019 --> 00:13:33.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, what's the point?

268
00:13:33.437 --> 00:13:36.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This ship will be joining
the mothball fleet next week.

269
00:13:36.232 --> 00:13:37.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I pretty much built this engine.

270
00:13:38.609 --> 00:13:40.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Plan to take care of it as long as I can.

271
00:13:43.239 --> 00:13:44.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

272
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:48.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Been a hell of a run, Malcolm.

273
00:13:50.621 --> 00:13:52.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I never thought it would come to an end.

274
00:13:56.168 --> 00:13:57.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All good things...

275
00:14:00.673 --> 00:14:03.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain thinks there'll be
another <i>Enterprise</i> before too long.

276
00:14:04.134 --> 00:14:05.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I imagine.

277
00:14:06.136 --> 00:14:07.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It won't be the same.

278
00:14:11.058 --> 00:14:12.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's OK.

279
00:14:15.354 --> 00:14:16.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on.

280
00:14:22.778 --> 00:14:24.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's sad.

281
00:14:24.488 --> 00:14:27.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander Tucker had no idea
he wouldn't make it back.

282
00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How reliable are your sources?

283
00:14:31.996 --> 00:14:34.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Shran] They're criminals,
but honorable ones.

284
00:14:34.623 --> 00:14:38.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They promise me that Talla's
being held here. At upper level 4.

285
00:14:38.878 --> 00:14:40.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you fashioned the amethyst?

286
00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:43.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The photograph you gave us
had poor resolution,

287
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:46.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I'm confident our
replication will look authentic.

288
00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:49.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Teneebian amethyst
they think I stole was flawless.

289
00:14:49.305 --> 00:14:51.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They'll undoubtedly have
magnifying equipment with them.

290
00:14:51.807 --> 00:14:54.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They'll need a spectral micrometer
to see it's a fabrication.

291
00:14:55.561 --> 00:14:57.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many do you expect to show up?

292
00:14:57.730 --> 00:14:59.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Computer, freeze program.
-[beeping]

293
00:15:02.443 --> 00:15:05.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-He's cute.
-Don't get any ideas.

294
00:15:05.404 --> 00:15:07.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reg will be furious if I'm late.

295
00:15:07.406 --> 00:15:08.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you gonna stay?
-[Riker] Yeah, for a little while.

296
00:15:09.116 --> 00:15:11.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good luck. Computer, arch.

297
00:15:16.582 --> 00:15:18.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, how long
before they reach Rigel X?

298
00:15:18.292 --> 00:15:20.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[computer] <i>Sixteen hours, 22 minutes.</i>

299
00:15:20.669 --> 00:15:23.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Advance to that point.
Stay in objective mode.

300
00:15:24.590 --> 00:15:26.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Move into a stationary orbit.

301
00:15:26.258 --> 00:15:27.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Travis] Aye, sir.

302
00:15:27.593 --> 00:15:29.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Put a team together.
Meet us in the launch bay.

303
00:15:29.803 --> 00:15:32.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tucker] Captain,
can I have a word with you?

304
00:15:35.351 --> 00:15:36.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can handle this without you.

305
00:15:37.269 --> 00:15:39.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Well, that's flattering.
-You know what I mean.

306
00:15:40.105 --> 00:15:42.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've got the biggest day
of your life coming up.

307
00:15:42.608 --> 00:15:44.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A lot of people are counting
on you being there.

308
00:15:44.777 --> 00:15:46.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I appreciate you worrying
about me, but I'll be fine.

309
00:15:46.403 --> 00:15:48.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't need to be putting
yourself in harm's way.

310
00:15:49.490 --> 00:15:51.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm telling you, we can take care of it.

311
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:53.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Rigel was the first place
we visited, remember?

312
00:15:53.661 --> 00:15:55.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now it's gonna be the last.

313
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:56.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Poetic justice.

314
00:15:57.581 --> 00:15:59.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why should you have all the fun?

315
00:16:05.172 --> 00:16:06.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're going through the troposphere.

316
00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:08.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Might get a little bumpy.

317
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:10.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you been down to see chef yet?

318
00:16:11.595 --> 00:16:13.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First thing this morning. You?

319
00:16:15.182 --> 00:16:16.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He talked about you.

320
00:16:17.559 --> 00:16:19.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Me?
-Us.

321
00:16:19.895 --> 00:16:20.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Tucker] What about us?

322
00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:24.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not important.

323
00:16:25.651 --> 00:16:28.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles] Why'd you bring it up, then?

324
00:16:28.654 --> 00:16:29.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[rumbling]

325
00:16:33.534 --> 00:16:34.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you ever miss me?

326
00:16:37.705 --> 00:16:38.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You mean...
-Yes.

327
00:16:40.249 --> 00:16:41.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know how long it's been?

328
00:16:42.251 --> 00:16:43.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what I asked you.

329
00:16:45.963 --> 00:16:47.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, um...

330
00:16:49.216 --> 00:16:50.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, I guess, sometimes.

331
00:16:54.763 --> 00:16:57.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I haven't thought about
those days in a long time.

332
00:16:57.307 --> 00:16:58.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Benefit of being a Vulcan.

333
00:17:00.978 --> 00:17:02.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
After speaking with chef,

334
00:17:02.521 --> 00:17:04.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I realized we may never
see each other again.

335
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:08.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you talking about?
-We're taking different assignments.

336
00:17:08.235 --> 00:17:10.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-There's no way of knowing--
-There's every way of knowing.

337
00:17:13.449 --> 00:17:15.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can guarantee you
we're not gonna lose touch.

338
00:17:17.786 --> 00:17:18.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stop thinking like that.

339
00:17:23.375 --> 00:17:27.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
However long it may be,
I believe I'm going to miss you.

340
00:17:30.507 --> 00:17:32.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] <i>Archer to Shuttlepod 2.</i>

341
00:17:32.342 --> 00:17:33.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go ahead, sir.

342
00:17:33.510 --> 00:17:35.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Archer] <i>Shran's made contact.</i>
<i>Everything's set.</i>

343
00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:37.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-I'll lead you in.</i>
-Understood.

344
00:17:56.492 --> 00:17:57.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Alien] Stop there.

345
00:18:00.662 --> 00:18:01.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Unless I'm mistaken,

346
00:18:01.955 --> 00:18:05.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you had no idea
where the amethyst was.

347
00:18:05.584 --> 00:18:06.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where's my daughter?

348
00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:09.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Funny how a missing child is
a way to jog the memory,

349
00:18:09.505 --> 00:18:10.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
eh, Shran?

350
00:18:10.422 --> 00:18:11.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where is she?

351
00:18:12.007 --> 00:18:13.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you were happily married.

352
00:18:14.218 --> 00:18:15.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who's the Vulcan?

353
00:18:15.761 --> 00:18:18.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not interested in your associates,
so don't question mine.

354
00:18:19.098 --> 00:18:20.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Put the case down and open it.

355
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:22.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We want the child first.

356
00:18:23.143 --> 00:18:24.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could shoot you both.

357
00:18:24.686 --> 00:18:27.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll never get this case open,
I promise you.

358
00:18:28.524 --> 00:18:31.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You let a female
negotiate for you, eh, Shran?

359
00:18:31.235 --> 00:18:32.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You heard her.

360
00:18:43.080 --> 00:18:46.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you all right?
-I'm hungry.

361
00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:47.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now open the case.

362
00:18:52.589 --> 00:18:54.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

363
00:19:07.563 --> 00:19:08.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Set it down.

364
00:19:16.405 --> 00:19:17.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now back up.

365
00:19:21.577 --> 00:19:23.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let her take the girl.

366
00:19:23.453 --> 00:19:25.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fine, but you stay.

367
00:19:25.998 --> 00:19:29.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One step, and this little blue beauty
won't have a father to come home to.

368
00:19:37.259 --> 00:19:41.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want you to go with T'pol.
You'll be safe with her.

369
00:19:42.055 --> 00:19:43.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She'll find you something to eat.

370
00:19:48.395 --> 00:19:49.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Obey your father.

371
00:20:02.367 --> 00:20:03.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now step back.

372
00:20:16.298 --> 00:20:17.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

373
00:20:25.349 --> 00:20:26.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

374
00:20:27.643 --> 00:20:29.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-[beeping]

375
00:20:42.199 --> 00:20:43.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[screams]

376
00:20:44.952 --> 00:20:47.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stand still, and you won't be harmed!

377
00:20:47.371 --> 00:20:48.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[shouts indistinctly]

378
00:21:12.521 --> 00:21:14.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ugh!

379
00:21:22.489 --> 00:21:24.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aah!

380
00:21:34.751 --> 00:21:35.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hold on!

381
00:21:39.256 --> 00:21:40.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

382
00:21:42.551 --> 00:21:43.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks, boss.

383
00:21:46.388 --> 00:21:47.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anytime.

384
00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:59.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're certain that it won't be a problem?

385
00:22:00.319 --> 00:22:01.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] I'll feel more comfortable

386
00:22:01.278 --> 00:22:04.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
getting you away
from your friends at warp 4.

387
00:22:04.698 --> 00:22:06.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shran] My shuttle may be slow,

388
00:22:06.700 --> 00:22:08.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but their ships can barely make warp 2.

389
00:22:08.660 --> 00:22:09.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All the same,

390
00:22:09.911 --> 00:22:11.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you'll be under your own power
by tomorrow night.

391
00:22:11.580 --> 00:22:12.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll contact your wife

392
00:22:12.622 --> 00:22:13.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and tell her to expect you
the next morning.

393
00:22:14.082 --> 00:22:16.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you my plan would
only take a few hours.

394
00:22:16.793 --> 00:22:17.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

395
00:22:18.045 --> 00:22:19.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

396
00:22:19.421 --> 00:22:22.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You should let phlox take a look at her
before you go to your quarters.

397
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:24.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whatever you say, captain.

398
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:26.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks, pink-skin.

399
00:22:26.595 --> 00:22:27.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

400
00:22:30.515 --> 00:22:32.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must be getting tired
of saving my life.

401
00:22:33.101 --> 00:22:35.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm glad I didn't take your
advice about not coming along.

402
00:22:35.437 --> 00:22:36.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, you and me both.

403
00:22:36.855 --> 00:22:39.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then again, you almost got
yourself killed down there.

404
00:22:39.566 --> 00:22:41.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wouldn't have gone over
too big at the ceremony.

405
00:22:41.818 --> 00:22:45.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Signing documents are easy.
Training a new engineer...

406
00:22:45.572 --> 00:22:47.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that can be a real pain in the ass.

407
00:22:59.836 --> 00:23:01.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[communicator beeps]
-[Data]<i> Data to counselor Troi.</i>

408
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:03.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, Data?

409
00:23:03.590 --> 00:23:05.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Data] <i>I was wondering if this might be</i>
<i>an appropriate time</i>

410
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:08.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to continue our discussion</i>
<i>on the long-term effects of space travel</i>

411
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:10.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>on my positronic net.</i>

412
00:23:10.639 --> 00:23:12.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can I give you a rain check?

413
00:23:12.599 --> 00:23:15.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Data]<i> You may, check me for rain</i>
<i>if you wish, counselor,</i>

414
00:23:15.519 --> 00:23:17.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but I assure you, I have no water in my--</i>

415
00:23:17.145 --> 00:23:18.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[door chimes]
-Data, I'll get back to you.

416
00:23:19.106 --> 00:23:20.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come in.

417
00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:23.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know it's past office hours.

418
00:23:23.652 --> 00:23:24.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it?

419
00:23:27.155 --> 00:23:29.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It won't be long before
they find the <i>Pegasus.</i>

420
00:23:29.324 --> 00:23:31.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You haven't made your decision.

421
00:23:33.120 --> 00:23:33.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Troi] The holodeck?

422
00:23:34.037 --> 00:23:35.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They rescued the Andorian's daughter.

423
00:23:35.872 --> 00:23:38.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, you're coming to the moment
of truth in there, as well.

424
00:23:39.167 --> 00:23:41.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I need you to promise
you'll keep this confidential.

425
00:23:42.587 --> 00:23:43.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know I will.

426
00:23:43.713 --> 00:23:45.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you know
about the treaty of Algeron?

427
00:23:45.882 --> 00:23:49.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
2311. It redefined
the Romulan neutral zone.

428
00:23:49.678 --> 00:23:51.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It also outlawed the use
of cloaking technology

429
00:23:51.805 --> 00:23:53.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on Starfleet vessels.

430
00:23:54.307 --> 00:23:55.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The <i>Pegasus?</i>

431
00:23:56.184 --> 00:23:58.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A secret group in Starfleet
security developed a prototype.

432
00:23:59.521 --> 00:24:01.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pressman was put in charge of testing it.

433
00:24:01.982 --> 00:24:04.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's why they're so eager to
find it before the Romulans do.

434
00:24:05.026 --> 00:24:07.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The accident, the 71 people who died...

435
00:24:08.113 --> 00:24:12.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-We were testing the cloaking device.
-It was covered up.

436
00:24:12.325 --> 00:24:14.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The nine of us who made it back
alive were sworn to secrecy.

437
00:24:15.704 --> 00:24:17.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you've lived with that for 12 years?

438
00:24:17.706 --> 00:24:20.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they want to pick the experiment up
where they left off.

439
00:24:20.500 --> 00:24:21.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you sure?

440
00:24:22.002 --> 00:24:23.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pressman told me himself.

441
00:24:24.754 --> 00:24:26.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What they're doing is wrong.

442
00:24:27.299 --> 00:24:29.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It could jeopardize the treaty.

443
00:24:31.011 --> 00:24:33.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you want to tell that
to Captain Picard.

444
00:24:33.722 --> 00:24:37.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I took an oath of secrecy.
Pressman still outranks the Captain.

445
00:24:38.727 --> 00:24:39.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Will...

446
00:24:41.521 --> 00:24:45.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You didn't get this far in your
career making easy decisions.

447
00:24:46.610 --> 00:24:49.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm confident you'll
make the right one now.

448
00:24:50.780 --> 00:24:51.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish I was.

449
00:24:53.325 --> 00:24:55.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Reed] He was anything but tactful.

450
00:24:56.119 --> 00:24:58.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What his countrymen
might refer to as a hick.

451
00:24:58.830 --> 00:24:59.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For the life of me,

452
00:24:59.748 --> 00:25:01.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I couldn't understand
what captain archer saw in him.

453
00:25:01.541 --> 00:25:03.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thinner. Roll it a little bit thinner,
like this.

454
00:25:03.710 --> 00:25:05.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, yeah, right.

455
00:25:05.629 --> 00:25:06.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Riker] Go on.

456
00:25:06.755 --> 00:25:08.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Reed sighs] That's about it, really.

457
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:11.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I used to think that first
impressions meant something.

458
00:25:11.885 --> 00:25:15.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess it's not always true.
You know, to be honest,

459
00:25:15.680 --> 00:25:17.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn't think he was
gonna last a month.

460
00:25:17.724 --> 00:25:19.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Old friend of the captain's or not.

461
00:25:20.769 --> 00:25:23.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And now, I can't imagine
what these last 10 years

462
00:25:23.855 --> 00:25:24.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
would have been like without him.

463
00:25:25.148 --> 00:25:26.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you ever find yourself
attracted to him?

464
00:25:28.318 --> 00:25:30.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Maybe a little.
-Hmm.

465
00:25:30.195 --> 00:25:32.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I never really thought he was my type.
-Hmm.

466
00:25:32.113 --> 00:25:33.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Didn't even graduate college,

467
00:25:33.573 --> 00:25:37.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he learned about engineering
working on boat engines, I think.

468
00:25:38.828 --> 00:25:40.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never cared much about languages.

469
00:25:40.830 --> 00:25:43.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snickers] Could barely speak English.

470
00:25:45.293 --> 00:25:46.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But he did have his moments.

471
00:25:49.005 --> 00:25:50.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I still find him kind of cute.

472
00:25:52.300 --> 00:25:54.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Keep that to yourself.
-Always do.

473
00:25:55.470 --> 00:25:57.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain said they've known
each other a long time.

474
00:25:57.389 --> 00:25:58.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Close to 20 years.

475
00:25:59.015 --> 00:26:02.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He taught the captain how to scuba dive
somewhere off the coast of Florida.

476
00:26:02.352 --> 00:26:04.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're pressing too hard.
Just slow, steady movement.

477
00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:06.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Oh, sorry.
-No need to apologize.

478
00:26:06.898 --> 00:26:08.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They've got a shorthand
they use sometimes.

479
00:26:08.900 --> 00:26:10.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Comes from spending so much time together.

480
00:26:11.069 --> 00:26:12.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did Trip ever take a swing at Picard?

481
00:26:13.530 --> 00:26:17.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-At who?
-Archer, Captain Archer?

482
00:26:17.284 --> 00:26:20.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not that I know of.
When push comes to shove,

483
00:26:20.578 --> 00:26:22.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander Tucker usually ends up
doing the right thing.

484
00:26:23.498 --> 00:26:24.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Travis] How am I doing?

485
00:26:24.416 --> 00:26:26.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, don't let it get too big.
Now fold it over.

486
00:26:26.793 --> 00:26:27.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There you go.

487
00:26:27.836 --> 00:26:29.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

488
00:26:30.005 --> 00:26:33.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And he's always pushing himself,
Often to the point of exhaustion.

489
00:26:33.258 --> 00:26:35.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's forced me to order him to
relax on more than one occasion.

490
00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:37.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To relax?

491
00:26:37.178 --> 00:26:41.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. Wasn't very keen on getting
neuropressure treatments from T'pol.

492
00:26:41.641 --> 00:26:44.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it was that or become
addicted to sedatives.

493
00:26:44.436 --> 00:26:46.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If I remember correctly, that's when...

494
00:26:46.896 --> 00:26:49.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Their romance began? Mm. Precisely.

495
00:26:49.649 --> 00:26:53.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One time, he became so exhausted,
I had to demand he get six hours sleep.

496
00:26:53.611 --> 00:26:57.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He negotiated it down to four.
A very stubborn young man.

497
00:26:58.199 --> 00:27:01.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah! [chuckles] I quite enjoy this.

498
00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:03.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So did he follow your orders?

499
00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:04.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Didn't have a choice.

500
00:27:06.916 --> 00:27:08.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've always got a choice.

501
00:27:10.337 --> 00:27:12.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, you think this alliance is gonna hold?

502
00:27:12.213 --> 00:27:13.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We better hope so.

503
00:27:13.131 --> 00:27:14.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are thousands
of planets within reach.

504
00:27:15.508 --> 00:27:16.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Got to start somewhere.

505
00:27:17.010 --> 00:27:18.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who would have guessed?

506
00:27:18.803 --> 00:27:20.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Vulcans and Andorians in the same bed.

507
00:27:22.432 --> 00:27:24.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Tellarites were never big
fans of the Andorians, either.

508
00:27:26.728 --> 00:27:28.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is a special bottle of whiskey.

509
00:27:29.105 --> 00:27:31.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Zefram Cochrane gave it to my father

510
00:27:31.149 --> 00:27:33.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the day they broke ground
at the warp 5 complex.

511
00:27:33.818 --> 00:27:37.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And here we are... toasting to warp 7.

512
00:27:38.990 --> 00:27:40.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here's to the next generation.

513
00:27:46.081 --> 00:27:47.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Written your speech yet?

514
00:27:47.540 --> 00:27:50.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I always cram before exams.
I've got three days left.

515
00:27:51.002 --> 00:27:52.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The biggest day of your life,

516
00:27:52.087 --> 00:27:53.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and you're gonna wait
until the night before.

517
00:27:53.963 --> 00:27:55.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's the biggest day of our lives.

518
00:27:55.382 --> 00:27:57.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I hate to contradict you, Captain.

519
00:27:57.842 --> 00:27:59.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're the man they're waiting to see.

520
00:27:59.928 --> 00:28:01.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[rumbling]

521
00:28:04.808 --> 00:28:07.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[beeps]
-Archer to the Bridge. What's going on?

522
00:28:07.268 --> 00:28:09.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[T'pol] <i>We're under attack, sir.</i>
<i>A small vessel.</i>

523
00:28:09.771 --> 00:28:10.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] Who are they?

524
00:28:10.688 --> 00:28:12.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[T'pol] <i>We don't know yet.</i>

525
00:28:12.190 --> 00:28:14.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[rumbling]
-[alarm ringing]

526
00:28:14.192 --> 00:28:15.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[T'pol] <i>Intruder alert.</i>

527
00:28:19.364 --> 00:28:21.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've come for Shran and the child.

528
00:28:21.616 --> 00:28:23.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you said their ship
couldn't catch up to us.

529
00:28:23.243 --> 00:28:24.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Remind me to mention that to Shran.

530
00:28:26.704 --> 00:28:28.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're leaving me very little choice.

531
00:28:28.706 --> 00:28:31.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shran left six hours ago. You're too late.

532
00:28:31.459 --> 00:28:33.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're lying.
His shuttle is still in your launch bay.

533
00:28:34.921 --> 00:28:36.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Kill him.
-[Tucker] Hold on! W-wait a minute!

534
00:28:36.840 --> 00:28:38.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Trip, I'll take care of this.
-The hell you will.

535
00:28:38.425 --> 00:28:39.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll bring you to Shran.
I know where he is.

536
00:28:39.884 --> 00:28:41.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I gave you an order, Commander.
-You heard me.

537
00:28:41.261 --> 00:28:42.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I said I'd bring you to Shran.
-Trip!

538
00:28:42.595 --> 00:28:44.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very well. Turn around, both of you!

539
00:28:44.222 --> 00:28:45.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Tucker] Hey, this guy's the Captain.
-That's enough.

540
00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:46.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Tucker] He's my boss.

541
00:28:46.933 --> 00:28:48.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I'm gonna disobey his order,
I don't want him coming along.

542
00:28:48.727 --> 00:28:49.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trip, that's enough!

543
00:28:49.644 --> 00:28:52.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Listen, I won't do this if you kill him,
but could you please shut him up!

544
00:28:57.068 --> 00:28:58.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stop.

545
00:28:58.611 --> 00:29:00.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can't expect me
to just leave him here alive.

546
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:03.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's out cold. He's not
gonna cause any trouble.

547
00:29:03.742 --> 00:29:04.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stay here.

548
00:29:04.659 --> 00:29:06.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If we're not back in 10 minutes, kill him.

549
00:29:06.828 --> 00:29:07.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Didn't you hear what I just said?

550
00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:11.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I won't help you if you kill him.
This might take longer than 10 minutes!

551
00:29:11.666 --> 00:29:14.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take me to Shran,
or I'll kill him right now!

552
00:29:14.210 --> 00:29:15.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
OK, OK!

553
00:29:16.379 --> 00:29:17.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got a better idea.

554
00:29:18.757 --> 00:29:21.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll bring Shran to us.
We don't have to go anywhere.

555
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:23.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

556
00:29:24.095 --> 00:29:25.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Be very careful.

557
00:29:27.390 --> 00:29:29.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can all come see for yourselves.

558
00:29:30.185 --> 00:29:32.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is just a comm station.

559
00:29:36.524 --> 00:29:39.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm gonna need to open this
so I can bypass the security protocols.

560
00:29:39.944 --> 00:29:40.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that OK?

561
00:29:40.987 --> 00:29:42.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As long as you keep your hands
where we can see them.

562
00:29:42.989 --> 00:29:43.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No problem.

563
00:29:44.866 --> 00:29:46.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeps]

564
00:29:57.253 --> 00:30:01.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All I need to do is connect this
to the relay inside that panel.

565
00:30:01.341 --> 00:30:03.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stop. Open it for him.

566
00:30:05.178 --> 00:30:08.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If there's a weapon in there,
you're going to die before your Captain.

567
00:30:13.186 --> 00:30:14.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Satisfied?

568
00:30:16.397 --> 00:30:17.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Proceed.

569
00:30:23.571 --> 00:30:25.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hurry up. You're running out of time.

570
00:30:26.449 --> 00:30:28.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's just one other thing
I need to tell you.

571
00:30:30.036 --> 00:30:31.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can all go straight to hell.

572
00:30:32.038 --> 00:30:34.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[screaming]

573
00:30:37.001 --> 00:30:39.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

574
00:30:57.146 --> 00:30:58.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trip?

575
00:31:15.331 --> 00:31:16.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[medic] He's not responding.

576
00:31:16.499 --> 00:31:17.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Phlox] Add two percent syntho-surfactant!

577
00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:18.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] Doctor.

578
00:31:18.585 --> 00:31:20.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Phlox] The plasma was super-heated.
It thermalized his lungs.

579
00:31:20.670 --> 00:31:22.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Initialize a hyperbaric chamber.

580
00:31:24.591 --> 00:31:29.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
S-sorry about the r-rifle butt.

581
00:31:29.637 --> 00:31:31.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[breathing heavily]

582
00:31:31.180 --> 00:31:33.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I was just trying to...
-I know, Trip.

583
00:31:34.517 --> 00:31:36.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just take it easy. Everything's all right.

584
00:31:36.436 --> 00:31:37.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We gonna be late?

585
00:31:37.979 --> 00:31:40.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Archer] No.
We're gonna be right on schedule.

586
00:31:40.857 --> 00:31:42.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll even have time to write my speech.

587
00:31:43.735 --> 00:31:44.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Great news.

588
00:31:46.029 --> 00:31:47.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait till they...

589
00:31:47.822 --> 00:31:48.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

590
00:31:49.032 --> 00:31:49.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

591
00:31:50.158 --> 00:31:51.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need to get him into the chamber now!

592
00:31:59.709 --> 00:32:00.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Clear!

593
00:32:50.426 --> 00:32:51.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Need any help?

594
00:32:53.763 --> 00:32:55.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, thank you.

595
00:32:56.349 --> 00:32:57.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For his parents?

596
00:33:00.061 --> 00:33:01.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Will they still be coming to the ceremony?

597
00:33:02.021 --> 00:33:04.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told them I thought Trip
wouldn't want it any other way.

598
00:33:14.242 --> 00:33:15.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't forget this.

599
00:33:19.455 --> 00:33:22.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I'd like to meet them.
-His parents?

600
00:33:23.251 --> 00:33:24.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, I'd like to meet them.

601
00:33:25.753 --> 00:33:26.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're a little eccentric.

602
00:33:29.007 --> 00:33:32.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you'll see where Trip
got his sense of humor.

603
00:33:33.761 --> 00:33:36.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My mother was somewhat eccentric, as well.

604
00:33:36.597 --> 00:33:37.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] I remember.

605
00:33:42.437 --> 00:33:46.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Trip told me, as the years went by,
that I would miss her less.

606
00:33:46.941 --> 00:33:51.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But he was wrong,
because I find myself missing her more.

607
00:33:54.532 --> 00:33:56.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs] Why would he tell me that?

608
00:33:57.660 --> 00:33:59.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

609
00:33:59.162 --> 00:34:01.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Time heals all wounds.

610
00:34:01.998 --> 00:34:05.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But absence makes the heart grow fonder.

611
00:34:05.543 --> 00:34:07.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess it's a little tricky.

612
00:34:10.715 --> 00:34:14.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Emotions have a way
of contradicting themselves.

613
00:34:15.970 --> 00:34:18.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you wonder why we suppress them?

614
00:34:21.893 --> 00:34:24.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When I took command 10 years ago,

615
00:34:24.771 --> 00:34:26.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I saw myself as an explorer.

616
00:34:27.732 --> 00:34:30.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought all the risks would be worth it.

617
00:34:31.486 --> 00:34:34.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because just beyond the next planet,
just beyond the next star,

618
00:34:34.781 --> 00:34:38.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
there would be something magnificent,

619
00:34:38.409 --> 00:34:39.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
something noble.

620
00:34:45.416 --> 00:34:49.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And now Trip is dead,
and I have to give a speech

621
00:34:49.545 --> 00:34:53.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
about how worthwhile it's all been.

622
00:34:55.093 --> 00:34:58.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Trip would be the first to say
it was worthwhile.

623
00:35:12.485 --> 00:35:14.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fried catfish with hush puppies.

624
00:35:15.154 --> 00:35:17.156 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Obviously, the captain mentioned
why I wanted to see you.

625
00:35:17.365 --> 00:35:18.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

626
00:35:18.741 --> 00:35:21.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Keep in mind, within a week,
I'll be eating the real thing.

627
00:35:21.202 --> 00:35:22.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Taking my folks down to mobile.

628
00:35:22.745 --> 00:35:24.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nothing like a challenge.

629
00:35:24.247 --> 00:35:25.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain asked for meatloaf, didn't he?

630
00:35:25.915 --> 00:35:26.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't spoken to him yet.

631
00:35:27.166 --> 00:35:30.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How about T'pol?
She won't be very cooperative.

632
00:35:30.336 --> 00:35:31.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wait and see.

633
00:35:32.171 --> 00:35:34.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've already started her plomeek broth.

634
00:35:34.173 --> 00:35:36.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All she has to do is choose
a few final ingredients.

635
00:35:37.051 --> 00:35:38.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She'll be down here in about an hour.

636
00:35:39.762 --> 00:35:41.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hear we're on our way to pick up Shran.

637
00:35:41.889 --> 00:35:43.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can you believe it?

638
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:45.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We all thought he was dead and gone.

639
00:35:45.309 --> 00:35:47.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, don't you think the Captain's
cutting it a little close?

640
00:35:47.687 --> 00:35:50.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You mean, getting back to San Francisco?

641
00:35:51.023 --> 00:35:53.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nah, he won't let anything
get in the way of that.

642
00:35:53.359 --> 00:35:54.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trust me.

643
00:35:56.112 --> 00:35:57.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can you spare one of those carrots?

644
00:35:57.905 --> 00:35:59.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-They're not peeled yet.
-That's OK.

645
00:36:03.578 --> 00:36:06.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know, he'd never admit it,

646
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:09.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but this thing means
a hell of a lot to him.

647
00:36:10.334 --> 00:36:13.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's real proud to be one of
the people signing this charter.

648
00:36:13.296 --> 00:36:15.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And he ought to be.

649
00:36:15.506 --> 00:36:18.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You sound like a lifetime member
of the Jonathan Archer fan club.

650
00:36:21.012 --> 00:36:24.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can count on one hand
the number of people I trust.

651
00:36:25.683 --> 00:36:27.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't mean trust like,

652
00:36:28.477 --> 00:36:32.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"I trust you aren't lying to me,"
or "i trust you won't steal my money."

653
00:36:32.899 --> 00:36:34.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm talking about
the kind of trust where...

654
00:36:36.068 --> 00:36:39.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know someone's not gonna
hurt you, no matter what,

655
00:36:39.530 --> 00:36:42.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
where you know they'll always
be there for you,

656
00:36:42.533 --> 00:36:44.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no matter how bad things get.

657
00:36:45.870 --> 00:36:47.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You ever know anybody like that?

658
00:36:48.497 --> 00:36:49.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

659
00:36:50.583 --> 00:36:51.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One or two.

660
00:36:54.754 --> 00:36:58.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I've got some packing
to do before I go back on duty.

661
00:37:00.176 --> 00:37:01.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You figured out what you're gonna do?

662
00:37:03.137 --> 00:37:03.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do?

663
00:37:04.096 --> 00:37:05.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You gonna sign onto another ship,

664
00:37:05.264 --> 00:37:07.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or are you gonna open up
that little restaurant

665
00:37:07.099 --> 00:37:08.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Berkshires you told me about?

666
00:37:08.684 --> 00:37:11.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, I haven't decided yet.
You got any advice?

667
00:37:11.520 --> 00:37:13.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles] Nope.

668
00:37:13.231 --> 00:37:14.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

669
00:37:17.485 --> 00:37:19.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I'm sure you'll make the right choice.

670
00:37:30.331 --> 00:37:32.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you certain these are the right seats?

671
00:37:32.667 --> 00:37:33.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Travis] Yep.

672
00:37:34.585 --> 00:37:36.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They don't seem very V.I.P. to me.

673
00:37:37.004 --> 00:37:39.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure the admiral
wanted us to have a view

674
00:37:39.215 --> 00:37:41.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that took in the scope of the occasion.

675
00:37:41.884 --> 00:37:43.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
From this distance,
you can't tell an Andorian

676
00:37:43.761 --> 00:37:45.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
from a Tellarite.

677
00:37:46.097 --> 00:37:48.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, have you given an answer
to Captain still well yet?

678
00:37:48.641 --> 00:37:50.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've asked him for a little more time,

679
00:37:50.476 --> 00:37:52.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
until captain archer decides
what he's going to be doing.

680
00:37:53.062 --> 00:37:56.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll bet you a month's pay
he'll be on the bridge of a new ship.

681
00:37:56.148 --> 00:37:58.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He won't be able to resist one
of those warp 7 beauties.

682
00:37:59.527 --> 00:38:01.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've heard he's already
been tapped for Admiral.

683
00:38:02.071 --> 00:38:05.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Malcolm's right.
They'll never keep him behind a desk.

684
00:38:05.616 --> 00:38:08.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's very wise of you to stick with him.

685
00:38:08.286 --> 00:38:10.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's exactly what I plan to do.

686
00:38:12.456 --> 00:38:13.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

687
00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:20.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, stand still.

688
00:38:21.924 --> 00:38:23.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you hadn't waited
until the last minute,

689
00:38:23.884 --> 00:38:26.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you would have had time
to memorize your speech.

690
00:38:26.887 --> 00:38:28.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You sound like my 9th-grade teacher.

691
00:38:28.639 --> 00:38:32.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are dignitaries here
from 18 different worlds.

692
00:38:32.476 --> 00:38:34.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles] It's a good sign.

693
00:38:34.937 --> 00:38:39.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wouldn't be surprised if this alliance
begins to expand before we know it.

694
00:38:39.984 --> 00:38:41.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You should be very proud
of yourself, Captain.

695
00:38:41.861 --> 00:38:44.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be proud of myself
if I get this speech out in one piece.

696
00:38:45.823 --> 00:38:47.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what I meant.

697
00:38:48.909 --> 00:38:51.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know what you meant, Phlox,
and I appreciate it.

698
00:38:52.955 --> 00:38:54.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But this is not about me.

699
00:38:54.832 --> 00:38:57.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why do so many humans
refuse to take credit

700
00:38:57.251 --> 00:38:58.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
where credit is due?

701
00:38:58.794 --> 00:39:02.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are times when modesty
and humility are quite illogical.

702
00:39:03.591 --> 00:39:04.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whenever you're ready, sir.

703
00:39:06.177 --> 00:39:09.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I've got three wives waiting.
I'd better go and join them.

704
00:39:11.474 --> 00:39:13.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd wish you good luck, Captain,

705
00:39:14.560 --> 00:39:18.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you've always had an ample supply.

706
00:39:18.439 --> 00:39:19.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, doctor.

707
00:39:26.322 --> 00:39:27.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Archer] You'd better get out there.

708
00:39:29.325 --> 00:39:31.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't want to miss me
screwing this thing up.

709
00:39:31.744 --> 00:39:34.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm going to remain down here,
if you don't mind.

710
00:39:35.331 --> 00:39:36.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You never did like crowds, did you?

711
00:39:42.671 --> 00:39:43.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You look...

712
00:39:45.299 --> 00:39:46.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
very heroic.

713
00:40:14.745 --> 00:40:16.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[applause]

714
00:40:31.095 --> 00:40:32.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is he nervous?

715
00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:33.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wouldn't you be?

716
00:40:34.056 --> 00:40:35.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, he'll be fine.

717
00:40:35.850 --> 00:40:38.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had to memorize this speech
in grammar school.

718
00:40:40.187 --> 00:40:41.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wish you could tell them all

719
00:40:41.730 --> 00:40:44.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that this alliance will
give birth to the Federation.

720
00:40:46.485 --> 00:40:48.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I'm ready to talk
to Captain Picard.

721
00:40:48.487 --> 00:40:50.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I should have done it a long time ago.

722
00:40:51.282 --> 00:40:52.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, I guess we're through here.

723
00:40:53.576 --> 00:40:54.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[applause]
-I guess we are.

724
00:40:55.578 --> 00:40:56.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

725
00:40:56.495 --> 00:40:57.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeps]

726
00:40:59.206 --> 00:41:00.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
...End program.

727
00:41:00.624 --> 00:41:01.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeps]

728
00:41:14.180 --> 00:41:17.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Picard] <i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

729
00:41:18.058 --> 00:41:21.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>These are the voyages</i>
<i>of the Starship </i>Enterprise.

730
00:41:21.645 --> 00:41:23.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Its continuing mission...</i>

731
00:41:24.523 --> 00:41:26.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kirk] <i>To explore strange new worlds,</i>

732
00:41:27.485 --> 00:41:30.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to seek out new life</i>
<i>and new civilizations...</i>

733
00:41:32.156 --> 00:41:35.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Archer] <i>To boldly go</i>
<i>where no man has gone before.</i>

